
👽 test linux/amd64

[EXPERIMENTAL]

A standalone tool to install CLI binaries using registry metadata.

USAGE


    $ atmos toolchain [flags]
    $ atmos toolchain [sub-command] [flags]


BUILT-IN COMMANDS

      add                 Add tools to .tool-versions file
      clean               Clean tools and cache directories
      du                  Show disk space usage for installed tools
      env                 Export PATH entries for installed tools in shell-specific format
      exec                Execute a tool with specified version
      get                 Get version information for a tool
      info                Show information about a tool
      install             Install CLI binaries from the registry
      list                List configured tools and their installation status
      path                Print PATH entries for installed tools (alias for 'toolchain env')
      registry [command]  Manage toolchain registries
      remove              Remove a tool or version from .tool-versions file
      search              Search for tools (alias to 'registry search')
      set                 Set default version for a tool
      uninstall           Uninstall a tool or all tools from .tool-versions
      which               Show path to installed tool binary

FLAGS

  -h, --help                   help for toolchain

      --tool-versions string   Path to tool-versions file (default .tool-versions)

      --toolchain-path string  Directory to store installed tools (default .tools)



Use atmos toolchain [command] --help for more information about a command.

Use --help=usage for examples or --help=all for all flags and full help.
